    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6238,
        6411
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> For information on the specific components and version information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>What's new in the Hadoop cluster versions provided by HDInsight?<ept id=\"p1\">][component-versioning]</ept>"
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6416,
        6443
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"ambari\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Ambari"
    },
    {
      "content": "Apache Ambari is for provisioning, managing and monitoring Apache Hadoop clusters.",
      "pos": [
        6445,
        6527
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It includes an intuitive collection of operator tools and a robust set of APIs that hide the complexity of Hadoop, simplifying the operation of clusters.",
      "pos": [
        6528,
        6681
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Manage HDInsight clusters using Ambari<ept id=\"p1\">](hdinsight-hadoop-manage-ambari.md)</ept> (Linux only), <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Monitor Hadoop clusters in HDInsight using the Ambari API<ept id=\"p2\">](hdinsight-monitor-use-ambari-api.md)</ept>, and <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://github.com/apache/ambari/blob/trunk/ambari-server/docs/api/v1/index.md\"&gt;</ph>Apache Ambari API reference<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        6682,
        7015
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7021,
        7078
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"avro\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Avro (Microsoft .NET Library for Avro)"
    },
    {
      "content": "The Microsoft .NET Library for Avro implements the Apache Avro compact binary data interchange format for serialization for the Microsoft .NET environment.",
      "pos": [
        7080,
        7235
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It uses <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.json.org/\"&gt;</ph>JavaScript Object Notation (JSON)<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph> to define a language-agnostic schema that underwrites language interoperability, meaning data serialized in one language can be read in another.",
      "pos": [
        7236,
        7473
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Detailed information on the format can be found in the &lt;a target=_\"blank\" href=\"http://avro.apache.org/docs/current/spec.html\"&gt;Apache Avro Specification<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        7474,
        7631
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The format of Avro files supports the distributed MapReduce programming model.",
      "pos": [
        7632,
        7710
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Files are “splittable”, meaning you can seek any point in a file and start reading from a particular block.",
      "pos": [
        7711,
        7818
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To find out how, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Serialize data with the Microsoft .NET Library for Avro<ept id=\"p1\">](hdinsight-dotnet-avro-serialization.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        7819,
        7938
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7945,
        7968
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"hdfs\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>HDFS"
    },
    {
      "content": "Hadoop Distributed File System (HDFS) is a distributed file system that, with MapReduce and YARN, is the core of the Hadoop ecosystem.",
      "pos": [
        7970,
        8104
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "HDFS is the standard file system for Hadoop clusters on HDInsight.",
      "pos": [
        8105,
        8171
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        8177,
        8211
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"hive\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Hive &amp; HCatalog"
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://hive.apache.org/\"&gt;</ph>Apache Hive<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph> is data warehouse software built on Hadoop that allows you to query and manage large datasets in distributed storage by using a SQL-like language called HiveQL.",
      "pos": [
        8213,
        8439
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Hive, like Pig, is an abstraction on top of MapReduce.",
      "pos": [
        8440,
        8494
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When run, Hive translates queries into a series of MapReduce jobs.",
      "pos": [
        8495,
        8561
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Hive is conceptually closer to a relational database management system than Pig, and is therefore appropriate for use with more structured data.",
      "pos": [
        8562,
        8706
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For unstructured data, Pig is the better choice.",
      "pos": [
        8707,
        8755
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Use Hive with Hadoop in HDInsight<ept id=\"p1\">](hdinsight-use-hive.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        8756,
        8819
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/Hive/HCatalog/\"&gt;</ph>Apache HCatalog<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph> is a table and storage management layer for Hadoop that presents users with a relational view of data.",
      "pos": [
        8821,
        9028
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In HCatalog, you can read and write files in any format for which a Hive SerDe (serializer-deserializer) can be written.",
      "pos": [
        9029,
        9149
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        9155,
        9182
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"mahout\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Mahout"
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://mahout.apache.org/\"&gt;</ph>Apache Mahout<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph> is a scalable library of machine learning algorithms that run on Hadoop.",
      "pos": [
        9184,
        9327
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Using principles of statistics, machine learning applications teach systems to learn from data and to use past outcomes to determine future behavior.",
      "pos": [
        9328,
        9477
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Generate movie recommendations using Mahout on Hadoop<ept id=\"p1\">](hdinsight-mahout.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        9478,
        9559
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        9565,
        9607
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"mapreduce\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>MapReduce and YARN"
    },
    {
      "content": "Hadoop MapReduce is a software framework for writing applications to process big-data sets in parallel.",
      "pos": [
        9608,
        9711
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A MapReduce job splits large datasets and organizes the data into key-value pairs for processing.",
      "pos": [
        9712,
        9809
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Apache YARN is the next generation of MapReduce (MapReduce 2.0, or MRv2) that splits the two major tasks of JobTracker - resource management and job scheduling/monitoring - into separate entities.",
      "pos": [
        9811,
        10007
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information on MapReduce, see <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://wiki.apache.org/hadoop/MapReduce\"&gt;</ph>MapReduce<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph> in the Hadoop Wiki.",
      "pos": [
        10009,
        10147
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To learn about YARN, see <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://hadoop.apache.org/docs/current/hadoop-yarn/hadoop-yarn-site/YARN.html\"&gt;</ph>Apache Hadoop NextGen MapReduce (YARN)<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        10148,
        10319
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        10325,
        10350
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"oozie\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Oozie"
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://oozie.apache.org/\"&gt;</ph>Apache Oozie<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph> is a workflow coordination system that manages Hadoop jobs.",
      "pos": [
        10351,
        10478
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It is integrated with the Hadoop stack and supports Hadoop jobs for MapReduce, Pig, Hive, and Sqoop.",
      "pos": [
        10479,
        10579
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It can also be used to schedule jobs specific to a system, like Java programs or shell scripts.",
      "pos": [
        10580,
        10675
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Use a time-based Oozie Coordinator with Hadoop<ept id=\"p1\">](hdinsight-use-oozie-coordinator-time.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        10676,
        10770
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        10776,
        10805
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"phoenix\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Phoenix"
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a  target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://phoenix.apache.org/\"&gt;</ph>Apache Phoenix<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph> is a relational database layer over HBase.",
      "pos": [
        10806,
        10921
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Phoenix includes a JDBC driver that allows users to query and manage SQL tables directly.",
      "pos": [
        10922,
